TODO: Make CI workflows gate downstream workflows

Current state:
- CI (ci.yml) is the main checker — lint, typecheck, tests, coverage, etc.
- No other workflow waits for CI to pass. They all trigger independently.
- Only existing dependencies: Release calls Package, Nightly CI calls CI.

Workflows to gate behind CI:
- Codecov — triggers on push only (not PRs), so workflow_run would work
- Demo screenshots — triggers on push and PRs
- Rodney demo — triggers on push and PRs
- Smoke tests — triggers on push and PRs
- Package — already gated (only called from Release or manual dispatch)

Options for gating:
1. workflow_run: only works on default branch, not on PRs
2. Move jobs into ci.yml with needs: — works on PRs but makes ci.yml bigger
3. For push-only workflows (Codecov), workflow_run is fine

Key context on secrets and PRs:
- PRs from the same repo (collaborators) get secrets
- PRs from forks do not get secrets
- workflow_run limitation is unrelated to secrets — it's a GitHub design choice

Next step: decide per-workflow whether to use workflow_run or merge into ci.yml.
